<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>About — Library Management System</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

  <style>
    /* Basic Reset */
    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body, html {
      height: 100%;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      background-color: #f4f4f4;
      color: #333;
    }

    /* Navbar */
    .navbar {
      background-color: #222;
      color: #fff;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 10px 20px;
    }
    .navbar .logo {
      font-size: 1.5em;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .navbar ul {
      list-style: none;
      display: flex;
      margin-left: auto;
    }
    .navbar ul li {
      margin-left: 20px;
    }
    .navbar ul li a {
      color: #fff;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 1em;
      padding: 5px 8px;
    }
    .navbar ul li a:hover {
      background-color: #555;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    /* Main content wrapper */
    .container {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 20px auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #fff;
      min-height: calc(100vh - (header-height + footer-height) );
      /* We’ll adjust header & footer heights manually */
    }

    .container h1 {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      font-size: 2.2em;
      color: #222;
    }

    .container p {
      font-size: 1.1em;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    /* Footer */
    .footer {
      background-color: #222;
      color: #fff;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 15px 20px;
      position: relative;
      bottom: 0;
      width: 100%;
    }

    /* For small screens */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .navbar ul {
        flex-direction: column;
        margin-left: 0;
      }
      .navbar ul li {
        margin: 10px 0;
      }
      .container {
        margin: 10px;
        padding: 15px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

    <%- include('../partials/header') %>

  <div class="container">
    <h1>About Library Management System</h1>
    <p>
      Welcome to the Library Management System. This system has been built to help users manage books, track issued and returned books, and maintain user profiles including students and librarians.
    </p>
    <p>
      Key features include book inventory, search by title/author/genre, issue/return workflow, reporting capabilities, and overdue fine calculation. The design is responsive and user-friendly.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our goal is to modernize library operations, reduce manual errors, and provide easy access to library resources for the users.
    </p>
  </div>

    <%- include('../partials/footer') %>

</body>
</html>